<div class="comment-text">
<p>It’s not a neo-Marxist analysis. He uses explicitly anti-Marxist thinkers like Pareto and Mosca whose analysis is rooted in looking at political or cultural power rather than who has the most wealth. Chicago school Public Choice Theory does a similar thing, they aren’t Marxists either. </p>
