<div class="comment-text">
<p>A compound error often occurs when comments concern economics or questions of calculation or comparison.</p>
<p>For instance, one recent comment suggests imports reduce inflation but wealthy benefit most.</p>
<p>Generally speaking inflation means central bank (CB) action that increases the supply of money (deflation the decrease of the supply of money). </p>
<p>The popular misconception is that inflation is the rise in prices, which is only the effect of CB action. Thus, the cause of higher prices was the CB increase in the money supply.</p>
<p>The cause of lower prices is CB action that reigns in money supply, in addition to all other trade factors such as cheaper imports that result in lower prices.</p>
<p>But why say those with wealth benefit more. This is simply not true.it is stale communist propaganda. It is a lie. It never was true. The benefit is the same.</p>
